### `src/api/auth.api.js`
```js
// Export these functions (use axiosInstance):
// register({ email, masterPasswordHash })  ‚Üí POST /auth/register
// login({ email, masterPasswordHash })     ‚Üí POST /auth/login
// refresh({ refreshToken })                ‚Üí POST /auth/refresh
// logout({ refreshToken })                 ‚Üí POST /auth/logout
```

### `src/api/vault.api.js`
```js
// getEntries()              ‚Üí GET /vault
// createEntry({ label, encryptedData })    ‚Üí POST /vault
// updateEntry(id, { label, encryptedData }) ‚Üí PUT /vault/:id
// deleteEntry(id)           ‚Üí DELETE /vault/:id
```

### `src/api/utils.api.js`
```js
// checkStrength(password)              ‚Üí POST /utils/strength
// checkBreach(password)                ‚Üí GET /utils/breach-check?password=xxx
```

---

## Step 5 ‚Äî Auth Context (`src/context/AuthContext.jsx`)

Store in Context:
- `accessToken` (from localStorage on init)
- `masterKey` (in-memory state only ‚Äî **never persisted**)
- `isAuthenticated` (derived from accessToken presence)

**`register(email, masterPassword)`:**
1. Call `hashForServer(masterPassword)` ‚Üí get `masterPasswordHash`
2. Call `register({ email, masterPasswordHash })`
3. Save `accessToken` + `refreshToken` to localStorage
4. Derive `masterKey = deriveMasterKey(masterPassword)` and store in context state

**`login(email, masterPassword)`:**
1. Same flow as register but call `login()` API
2. Derive and store `masterKey` in memory

**`logout()`:**
1. Call `logout()` API with stored refreshToken
2. Clear localStorage
3. Set `masterKey` to null in state
4. Redirect to `/login`

---

## Step 6 ‚Äî Pages

### `src/pages/Register.jsx`
Fields: Email, Master Password, Confirm Password

On submit:
1. Validate passwords match
2. Call `auth.register(email, masterPassword)` from context
3. On success ‚Üí navigate to `/dashboard`
4. Show error messages inline

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Show a warning: *"Your master password cannot be recovered. We never store it."*

---

### `src/pages/Login.jsx`
Fields: Email, Master Password

On submit:
1. Call `auth.login(email, masterPassword)` from context
2. On success ‚Üí navigate to `/dashboard`

---

### `src/pages/Dashboard.jsx`

On mount:
1. Fetch all vault entries via `getEntries()`
2. For each entry: `decryptData(entry.encryptedData, masterKey)` to get `{ site, username, password }`
3. Render a list of `<VaultEntry>` cards

If `masterKey` is null (user refreshed page):
- Show a **"Re-enter master password"** prompt
- On submit, re-derive `masterKey` and try decrypting one known entry to validate

---

## Step 7 ‚Äî Components

### `VaultEntry.jsx`
Props: `{ label, decryptedData, onEdit, onDelete }`

Render:
- Label (site name)
- Username (show/hide toggle)
- Password field (hidden by default, reveal on button click)
- Copy-to-clipboard button for password
- Edit / Delete buttons

### `AddEntryModal.jsx`
Fields: Label (site name), Username, Password

On submit:
1. Build plaintext object: `{ username, password }`
2. `encryptData({ username, password }, masterKey)` ‚Üí get ciphertext
3. Call `createEntry({ label, encryptedData: ciphertext })`
4. Close modal, refresh list

### `StrengthMeter.jsx`
Props: `{ password }`

On every keystroke:
1. Call `checkStrength(password)` API (debounce 300ms)
2. Show a colored progress bar (score 0‚Äì100)
3. Show feedback tips below

---

## Step 8 ‚Äî Routing (`src/App.jsx`)

```jsx
<Routes>
  <Route path="/login" element={<Login />} />
  <Route path="/register" element={<Register />} />
  <Route path="/dashboard" element={<PrivateRoute><Dashboard /></PrivateRoute>} />
  <Route path="/" element={<Navigate to="/dashboard" />} />
</Routes>
```

**`PrivateRoute`:** Check `isAuthenticated` from context. If false ‚Üí redirect to `/login`.

---

## Step 9 ‚Äî Security Checklist

| Rule | Why |
|---|---|
| Never store `masterKey` outside memory | If localStorage leaks, vault stays encrypted |
| Always `decryptData` client-side only | Backend never sees plaintext |
| Debounce breach-check API calls | Avoid hammering HIBP on every keystroke |
| Clear clipboard after 30s on copy | Prevent clipboard sniffing |
| Session timeout on idle (optional) | Clear `masterKey` after 5min inactivity |

---

## Step 10 ‚Äî Environment & Build

```bash
# Development
npm run dev

# Production build
npm run build
```

Set `VITE_API_URL` to your deployed backend URL for production.

